      "span_text": "Nevertheless, 20-25% of patients with fractured scaphoid have positive findings in physical examination but normal radiology reports following direct X-ray.  Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) is a more appropriate diagnostic modality for demonstration of a scaphoid fracture, but the high costs and limited availability, as well as the long duration of the examination, have been a major hindrance to a wide application of MR imaging for wrist and hand injury."
